# Section 1 — Executive Summary

This report presents a data analysis of the Human Resources dataset developed by Dr. Carla Patalano, focusing on recruitment efficiency, employee turnover, hiring quality, and workforce trends. The objective of the analysis is to identify operational gaps within recruitment and retention processes and provide data-driven recommendations to improve workforce stability and hiring effectiveness. The analysis answers key business questions related to employee termination rates, recruitment source performance, departmental hiring trends, and factors influencing employee retention. Primary stakeholders for this analysis include the HR Manager, Recruitment Team, and Chief Executive Officer (CEO), who can use these insights to optimize hiring strategies, reduce turnover costs, improve employee performance outcomes, and support long-term organizational planning.

