# Section 3 — SQL Queries

## BQ-001: Which department has the highest employee turnover rate?

```sql
-- This query calculates employee turnover by department
SELECT 
    Department,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN Termd = 1 THEN Employee_Name END) AS Terminated_Employees,
    COUNT(Employee_Name) AS Total_Employees,
    ROUND(
        (COUNT(CASE WHEN Termd = 1 THEN Employee_Name END) * 100.0) /
        COUNT(Employee_Name),
        2
    ) AS Turnover_Rate_Percentage
FROM HRDataset
GROUP BY Department
ORDER BY Turnover_Rate_Percentage DESC;
```

---

## BQ-002: What is the average time-to-hire across departments?

```sql
-- This query calculates average days between application and hire date
SELECT 
    Department,
    AVG(DATEDIFF(day, ApplicationDate, DateofHire)) AS Avg_Time_To_Hire_Days
FROM HRDataset
WHERE ApplicationDate IS NOT NULL
    AND DateofHire IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY Department
ORDER BY Avg_Time_To_Hire_Days DESC;
```

---

## BQ-003: Is there a correlation between recruitment source and employee performance?

```sql
-- This query analyzes employee performance by recruitment source
SELECT 
    RecruitmentSource,
    PerformanceScore,
    COUNT(Employee_Name) AS Employee_Count
FROM HRDataset
GROUP BY RecruitmentSource, PerformanceScore
ORDER BY RecruitmentSource, Employee_Count DESC;
```

---

## BQ-004: Which recruitment sources produce the highest quality hires?

```sql
-- This query joins recruitment and employee performance data
-- to identify the most effective recruitment sources

SELECT 
    r.RecruitmentSource,
    AVG(e.EmpSatisfaction) AS Avg_Satisfaction,
    AVG(e.SpecialProjectsCount) AS Avg_Project_Count,
    COUNT(e.Employee_Name) AS Total_Hires
FROM RecruitmentData r
JOIN EmployeePerformance e
    ON r.EmployeeID = e.EmployeeID
GROUP BY r.RecruitmentSource
ORDER BY Avg_Satisfaction DESC;
```

---

## BQ-005: What are the key factors associated with employee termination?

```sql
-- This query identifies factors linked with employee termination
SELECT 
    MaritalDesc,
    Position,
    AVG(Absences) AS Avg_Absences,
    AVG(EngagementSurvey) AS Avg_Engagement_Score,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN Termd = 1 THEN Employee_Name END) AS Terminated_Count
FROM HRDataset
GROUP BY MaritalDesc, Position
HAVING COUNT(CASE WHEN Termd = 1 THEN Employee_Name END) > 5
ORDER BY Terminated_Count DESC;
```

